Diagnosis.
(amended; see Huber 2015). Easily distinguished from similar congeners (

M. pallens

, 

M. azureus

, 

M. brasiliensis

) by slender procursus (compare 
Figs 271–279
) (but see Note below) and by epigynum without median pocket (Huber 2015: figs 26, 60; 
Fig. 296
).

Note.
A very similar species occurs in Paraná state (Fazenda Experimental Gralha Azul, 25.667°S, 49.270°W; specimens in ZFMK Ar 19104 and Br10-59; “Br10-4” in 
Fig. 730
). Males seem to be slightly larger but otherwise identical in all details; females differ by having a shallow but distinct median epigynal pocket (
Fig. 297
).
